    • Method Detail

      • valueEquals

        public static boolean valueEquals(java.lang.Object o1,
                                  java.lang.Object o2)
        Compares two objects based on their values. The method uses the following rules:
        1. Two nulls are equal
        2. If o1 and o2 are both strings, they are equal if their text is equal
        3. If o1 and o2 are both numbers, they are equal if their conversion into a double returns the same value
        4. Otherwise, the default equals() method is invoked
        Parameters:
        o1 - The first object
        o2 - The second object
        Returns:
        true or false according to the rules mentioned above

      • castToDouble

        public static double castToDouble(java.lang.Object o)
        Attempts to create a double number out of an object.
        • If o is a Number, it returns o.doubleValue()
        • If o is a String, it is parsed as a double; 0 is returned if the parsing fails
        • If o is anything else, 0 is returned
        Parameters:
        o - The object
        Returns:
        A number, created according to the rules above

      • castToInteger

        public static int castToInteger(java.lang.Object o)
        Attempts to create an int number out of an object.
        • If o is a Number, it returns o.intValue()
        • If o is a String, it is parsed as an int; 0 is returned if the parsing fails
        • If o is anything else, 0 is returned
        Parameters:
        o - The object
        Returns:
        A number, created according to the rules above
